main event: An unidentified aerial object sighting occurred on March 17, 1966, in New Palestine, Indiana, where observers reported seeing two red lights with no distinguishable shape.
interesting points: The object appeared to be hovering about 30-40 feet above the ground.,Observers could not determine the shape of the object, only that it had two red lights about 15-20 feet apart., A witness reported it flying in a crooked S-like formation., The sighting was corroborated by several witnesses in the area., The report concluded that the data collected was insufficient for evaluation.
sighted object: two red lights about 15-20 feet apart
witness description: A resident from New Palestine, Indiana traveling with family.
